  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that is, because there was a ban on fraternization with Germans, meant to keep our GIs from taking up with-- with German girls, I had a difficult time to visit Gerda, because I would take my Jeep-- this was, you know, quite a distance outside of Munich-- take my Jeep and-- and go to the house I had found for-- for the two of them, and then couldn't leave it outside the house, because the-- the MPs that were roaming the city would have found the-- the Jeep and thought that here's somebody who is trying to fraternize with Germans, so that I always had to find a way of hiding the Jeep when I wanted to visit.",
      "word_count": 119
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Funny now, but at the time, it presented a problem.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And from then on, our relationship developed even closer, and-- until [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] September, when-- at which point I had enough points to-- to be sent home.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I suddenly got orders to get ready to be discharged from the service to be sent home, discharged from the service.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, at that point, Gerda and I got engaged.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was September 13th.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But there were no consulates in Germany that would have allowed her to leave also.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at any rate, the-- the whole situation was so-- in such a state of flux, where you didn't know-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you didn't know when she could come exactly.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But also I didn't know where I would settle down once I was back in the States.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't know would I stay in Buffalo or would I go to New York City, where both my sister and my brother lived by then?",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
